# Dead Stats — Project Conventions

## JS Patterns

- Use `async/await` for all API calls; never raw `.then()` chains
- Return `{ error: 'message' }` objects from data functions — never throw to the UI layer
- Cache the heroes list in a module-level variable (`let cachedHeroes = null`)
- All DOM manipulation lives in `popup.js`; no inline scripts in HTML

## Error Handling

```js
// ✅ GOOD — always catch network failures separately
try {
  const res = await fetch(url);
  if (!res.ok) return { error: `API error ${res.status}` };
  return await res.json();
} catch {
  return { error: 'Unable to fetch stats – check your connection' };
}

// ❌ BAD — letting errors bubble to the UI
const data = await fetch(url).then(r => r.json());
```

## Quality Gates

Before marking any feature done, all gates in `spec.md` must pass. Run:
```bash
npm test && npm run build
```

## Custom Commands

- `/task` — Break the request into a numbered todo list before writing any code. Use for anything touching 2+ files.
- `/fast` — Skip planning; implement the simplest solution immediately. Use for single-line fixes.
- `/remember` — Append the key decision or fact to CLAUDE.md under a "Session Notes" heading.
